

## LANDING 2 — YOUKAI MOUNTAIN

They land on a slope.

Rocky, steep, wreathed in mist. The air is colder than it should be and smells like pine and altitude. For about three seconds it is almost peaceful.

Then the mist moves, and there are people in it. White hair. Swords. The kind of stillness that means they've been there the whole time and chose to let themselves be seen.

The players are surrounded before they've fully registered where they are.

One of the tengu speaks. The tone doesn't require translation.

> **DM:** You have a few seconds before this goes somewhere uncomfortable. What do you do?

*If they do nothing, reach for anything, or say the wrong thing — the tension holds, swords stay raised.*

Then, from further up the slope, someone comes running.

Green hair. Shrine maiden clothes. Arms already up before she reaches them.

> "I've got this! They're outsiders — they're not threats, I promise, I can vouch for them!"

She is slightly out of breath. She is beaming.

Her name is Sanae Kochiya, and she looks at the players the way someone looks at a thing they have been hoping to find for a long time.

The tengu lower their weapons. Reluctantly.

> "You have one hour," one of them says. "Get them off the mountain."

Sanae turns to the players with the energy of someone who has about forty questions and is trying to decide which one to lead with.

> "Okay so — you're from outside, right? Like actually outside? What year is it? No wait, more importantly — are you hurt? Did the crossing feel weird? It felt weird when I did it but that was different circumstances—"

